        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Hereditary mixed polyposis syndrome (HMPS) describes an autosomal dominantly inherited large-bowel disease characterized by the presence of a mixture of hyperplastic atypical juvenile and adenomatous polyps that are associated with an increased risk of developing colorectal cancer if left untreated."
        },
